  "prompt": "My girlfriend and I took a break. About two months later she told me she made out with her ex during our break. What do I do?",
  "response": "Navigating a situation like this can be emotionally challenging, and there\u2019s no one-size-fits-all answer. Here are some steps to help you process this and decide what to do next:\n\n### 1. **Reflect on Your Feelings**\n   - Take time to understand how this news affects you. Are you hurt, angry, confused, or indifferent? Acknowledge your emotions without judgment.\n   - Consider the nature of your break: Were there clear boundaries or expectations about what would happen during this time?\n\n### 2. **Communicate Openly**\n   - Have an honest conversation with your girlfriend. Express how you feel and ask her to share her perspective.\n   - Ask clarifying questions if needed, such as why she chose to reconnect with her ex and what it means for her now.\n\n### 3. **Assess the Relationship**\n   - Reflect on the overall health and future of your relationship. Is this a dealbreaker for you, or can you move past it?\n   - Consider whether the break and her actions during it have revealed deeper issues that need to be addressed.\n\n### 4. **Set Boundaries**\n   - If you decide to continue the relationship, establish clear boundaries moving forward to rebuild trust.\n   - Discuss what \u201ctaking a break\u201d means in the future, if it ever comes up again, to avoid misunderstandings.\n\n### 5. **Work on Trust**\n   - Trust may have been impacted by this revelation. If you want to move forward, focus on rebuilding it through consistent actions and open communication.\n   - Be patient with yourself and your partner as you navigate this.\n\n### 6. **Seek Support**\n   - Talk to a trusted friend, family member, or therapist to process your emotions and gain perspective.\n   - If the relationship is important to both of you, couples counseling could help address underlying issues.\n\n### 7. **Make a Decision**\n   - After reflecting and communicating, decide whether you\u2019re willing to move forward or if this is a sign that the relationship isn\u2019t right for you.\n   - Remember, it\u2019s okay to prioritize your emotional well-being and choose what\u2019s best for you.\n\nUltimately, this is about what you\u2019re comfortable with and what aligns with your values and goals for the relationship. Take your time and make a decision that feels right for you.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
